        "body": "<p>Given the following JSON object example:<\/p>\n\n<pre><code>jsonObject.put(\"Names\", jsonArray);\n\ntry{\n\n    FileWriter jsonFileWriter = new FileWriter(jsonFilePath);\n    jsonFileWriter.write(jsonObject.toJSONString());\n    jsonFileWriter.flush();\n    jsonFileWriter.close();\n\n    System.out.print(jsonObject);\n\n} catch (IOException e){\n    e.printStackTrace();\n}\n<\/code><\/pre>\n\n<p>I am using JAVA Server and Client that are using sockets, can I use <\/p>\n\n<pre><code>os.println(jsonObject);\n<\/code><\/pre>\n\n<p>To send it to the client, or is there another method to send the JSON object?<\/p>\n",
